    "title": "UK and Ireland RADAR-derived instantaneous surface rain rate estimate composite (5km) ",	
    "description": "The UK and Ireland RADAR-derived instantaneous surface rain rate estimate composite is a 'best data' Cartesian-gridded composite across UK and Ireland of RADAR-estimated surface precipitation rates with all corrections applied. It is produced by the Met Office's weather radar central processing system. This bulletin is in BUFR format, and the data have a resolution of 5km.",	
